oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Bull Run Steam Plant construction
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A view of the TVA's Bull Run Steam Plant construction. Skimmer dam construction, the skimmer wall directs warm upper lake water away from the plant intake, permits cooler water from the bottom to flow through to the intake for condenser cooling.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Construction; Structural systems; Power plants; Public utility companies
